The paper discusses the PageRank algorithm, which is a fundamental technique in web information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions bibliometrics, sociometry, and econometrics, which are related to digital libraries (cs.DL), social networks (cs.SI), and computational finance (cs.CY), respectively. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses the development and success of the Google search engine.
